		</div>
	</div>
	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64552869"><p>If you're an intensive and/or picky user of MS Office, install LibreOffice on your Windows machine and see how you get along. Some people - including my wife - find that they either can't stand the way Libre does things, or that file compatibility with MS Office is not quite as seamless as you need for collaborations. That applies to other software as well - find the nearest Linux equivalents of programs you rely on and see if they meet your needs.</p><p>That brings up another point - install Linux as a Virtual Ma<span class="substr"> </span></p></div>
	</div>

